nce on September 19, 2020, at Uniosun Road Oke Baale Osogbo. Defence Counsel, Okobe Najite, in an oral application urged the court to admit the accused person to bail in the most liberal term. In her ruling, Magistrate Awodele ordered the remand of the accused person in Ilesa correctional facility and adjourned the matter till  December 21, 2020, for ruling on bail. Vanguard News Nigeria A Septuagenarian, Adewale Murtala, was on Friday arraigned before an Osogbo Magistrates’ Court for allegedly duping the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG). October 21, 2016 In "News" An Osogbo Senior Magistrate’s Court, yesterday, ordered that a 32-year-old man, Kelvin Ighodalo, be remanded in prison, for allegedly stealing the mobile telephone handset of Governor Rauf Aregbesola of Osun State. July 10, 2012 In "News" An Oshogbo Magistrate court yesterday ordered a former Commissioner for Finance and Economic Development in the administration of former Governor Olagunsoye Oyinlola, Mr Moses Adetoyese Ojo, to be remanded in prison custody for allegedly defrauding the state to the tune of N60 million while serving as a Commissioner in the… March 2, 2012 In "News"